<p>According to Muhammad and the Quran, there is a belief that:</p>
<ol>
<li>An ocean of sweet water exists above the seven heavens.</li>
<li>This sweet water of rain falls from that ocean above the heavens onto the Earth.</li>
<li>It is the same ocean upon which the throne of Allah rests.</li>
<li>Additionally, there are mountains of snow in the heavens, from which Allah sends hail.</li>
</ol>
<p>This portrayal aligns with a Flat Earth model, where the seven heavens are envisioned as a canopy above the flat Earth.</p>
<p>It is worth noting that Muhammad seemingly adopted this model of rain and the flat Earth from the Bible, which, in turn, have drawn inspiration from earlier civilizations.</p>
